0–1586","1470–1530":"1470–1530","1475–Female":"1475–Deceased","1495":"1495","1550":"1550","1470":"1470","1503":"1503","1533":"1530","1521":"1521","1586":"1586","1553":"1553","1530":"1530","1475":"1475","1518":"1518","1517":"1517","1549":"1549","England":"England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Bury St Edmunds, Suffolk, England":"Bury St Edmunds, Suffolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Kilham","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Kilham (ER Yorks), Kilham in Cantley (WR Yorks), or Kilham in Kirknewton (Northumb)."],"variants":[{"name":"Killham","meanings":["English: from any of several places in northern England called Kilham, most of which are recorded as <i>Killum</i> in medieval documents, from an Old English prepositional phrase meaning ‘at the kilns’."]},{"name":"Killam","meanings":["English (mainly Yorkshire): variant of <b>Kilham</b>, a habitational name from any of the places in Northumberland and Yorkshire, so named either from Old English <i>cylnum</i> ‘(at) the kilns’, dative plural of <i>cyln</i>, or from Old English <i>cyln</i> ‘kiln’ or the personal name <i>Cylla</i> + Old Norse <i>holmr</i> ‘small island, water meadow’. This surname is rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":54,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Walter Kilham was born in 1495, in Suffolk, England, his father, Peter Kilham, was 25 and his mother, Susan Kilham, was 20. He married Mary Alice Leister in 1517, in Suffolk, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1550, in his hometown, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1495–1550":"1495–1550","1503–1553":"1503–1553","1518–Male":"1518–Surnud","1521–Female":"1521–Surnud","1530–1586":"1530–1586","1470–1530":"1470–1530","1475–Female":"1475–Surnud","1495":"1495","1550":"1550","1470":"1470","1503":"1503","1533":"1530","1521":"1521","1586":"1586","1553":"1553","1530":"1530","1475":"1475","1518":"1518","1517":"1517","1549":"1549","England":"England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Bury St Edmunds, Suffolk, England":"Bury St Edmunds, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1495–1550":"1495–1550","1503–1553":"1503–1553","1518–Male":"1518–Kuollut","1521–Female":"1521–Kuollut","1530–1586":"1530–1586","1470–1530":"1470–1530","1475–Female":"1475–Kuollut","1495":"1495","1550":"1550","1470":"1470","1503":"1503","1533":"1530","1521":"1521","1586":"1586","1553":"1553","1530":"1530","1475":"1475","1518":"1518","1517":"1517","1549":"1549","England":"England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Bury St Edmunds, Suffolk, England":"Bury St Edmunds, Suffolk, England"},"fr":{"1495–1550":"1495–1550","1503–1553":"1503–1553","1518–Mal